The paper deals with the computational complexity of the game Mastermind, which involves guessing a secret code based on feedback from previous guesses. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis also involves data structures (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the result has implications for the memory-restricted black-box complexity of a function class, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
